While Ri repeated well-known North Korean complaints about Washington's resistance to the possibility of a "gradual" approach to denuclearization, whereby North Korea would be rewarded as it progressed gradually in the process, his statement was significant in that it did not completely rule out unilateral denuclearization, as Pyongyang did in the past.
Ri was quoted in Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump's joint communiqué at the first summit that took place between a sitting U.S. president and a North Korean leader in Singapore on June 12, when Kim promised to work on "denuclearizing the Korean peninsula", while Trump promised guarantees for North Korea's security.
North Korea seeks to officially end the 1950-53 Korean war, but the United States has said that Pyongyang must first "deliver" its nuclear weapons.
